    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-09-14T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-09-14T06:00:00-05:00" n="337"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d337">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">868.48/96: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The High Commissioner at Constantinople</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bristol</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Constantinople</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-09-14T14:00:00+03:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 14, 1922—2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 6:10 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>184. Following from Davis repeated for the information of Department and American
                    Red Cross: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“Twelfth. Only way to picture this refugee situation imagine refugees,
                            some single, families, groups few to five thousand hidden in
                            institutions or huddled here, there, moving, panic stricken, when
                            irregulars begin shooting them. We are urging authorities to protect and
                            place them in camp. These answer will do so but animosity of troops so
                            great difficult and urge us place before foreign governments necessity
                            of taking them away. Until this done one of worst refugee problems
                            possible contemplate will continue here. Authorities say have not enough
                            food for army so unable to help feed refugees. Unable as yet report on
                            situation on islands probably can soon. Grave. Davis.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>Latest information from Mudania to the effect refugee situation here [<hi
                        rend="italic">there</hi>] fully as bad as Smyrna.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bristol</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
